Installation:
- Run install.sh to install required Python modules and Node.js components.
- (TODO) Update crontab with hardware control script

Initial configuration:
- Rename app/cfg/config-example.yaml to app/cfg/config.yaml with your own settings.
- Set absolute path to config.yaml in app/lib/NidoConfig.py.

Generating a test build:
- npm run build

Generating a production build
- npm run build-prod

Running the application:
- sudo python app/nido.py
  Note: sudo is required due to hardware access to GPIO pins
